….And that’s how my 2022 went 💕

I pretty much stayed home (thanks to COVID) and decided to make use of it by learning to create better content and do a lot of “self help” work…

Throughout 2022 my main goal was SELF ACCEPTANCE though... Ever since I started my Instagram beauty account, my confidence took a huge hit seeing all the “perfection” everywhere making me think of how much I was lacking in life..but what opened my eyes was realizing that what we see on social media is very curated to specific audience (hence following aesthetics) and perfectly edited to look “picture perfect”…… This year I learned to accept me as is (makeup free , no filters — flaws and all) and not fall for the social media “perfection” cause that ISN’T reality…I am also grateful for the relationship I created with various brands and the opportunities I got. Thanks to those of you that stuck with me and enjoyed my posts.. I can’t wait to see what next year brings…stay blessed 💖

#soldejaneirogiftedme @soldejaneiro their super popular “Brazilian Crush Cheirosa 68” Perfume Mist!! I already own the “Beija Flor Elasti-Cream” which contains the same scent as Cheirosa 68, and I love it so much!! The fragrance smells very sweet (like flowers, cotton candy and lychee)! Cheirosa 68 is supposed to be a dupe for the MFK’s Baccarat Rouge 540, but I don’t think it’s an exact dupe but they do have similar “sweet” vibes to them.  Definitely a great alternative! When it comes to lasting power, it’s like a typical “mist” and lasts a few hours before you have to reapply. Remember, body sprays don’t contain the same strength of perfume concentration as EDT or EDP so it lasts less time. 

Overall, I’m a fan and I love the way this spray bottle looks on my vanity :) If you love sweet scents then you will enjoy this spray for sure!!
